{
    "version": "http://ipuz.org/v2",
    "kind": ["http://ipuz.org/crossword#1"],
    "title": "The Three-Boddy Problem",
    "copyright": "2026 The Rackenfracker",
    "author": "dadgumituh and jmsr525",
    "editor": "Andy Yingst",
    "explanation": "<br>POWER GRID is also the name of a first-ballot great board game by Friedemann Friese. The puzzle’s clues all start with F as a nod to Friese's convention for naming his games (in his native Germany, Power Grid is called Funkenschlag).<br><br><i>Fuses</i><br>A. MERE: Basic | SKEE: kind of ball<br>B. PARSE: Break down | EARED: like, to give an obvious example, Dumbo<br>C. WEPT: Cried | WREAKED: let slip<br>D. YANKED: Quickly drew | TREND: fashion<br> E. HERR: German address | SOUNDER: in better shape<br>F. GEAR: It might be first, second, or even fifth | GRAN: relative<br>G. PRIME: Main | PHASES: parts<br>H. SATIN: Silky smooth | BASIE: jazz musician<br>I. ROCKS: Stone | HOPED: has aspirations<br><br><i>Across</i><br>1. GRIME: G + RIME<br>4. BAT + H[appy]<br>6. HYPED: HYP[hen]ED<br>7. \\AIR\\<br>8. FREAKED: F(RE)AKE + D.<br>10. SKEW: \\SKU\\<br>11. “THE Y.”<br>14. PAUSE: PA + USE<br>17. SE[st[a]ge]TS <i>&lit.</i><br>19. BRAN: B(R[iboflavin])AN<br>20. SOUNDED: SO + UNDE[a]D<br>21. ON + C.E.<br>22. BASTE: (BEATS)* <i>See 4-down.</i><br>23. [r ->]USE(-> R)<br>24. TRENT: TRIPPED -> T + RIPPED -> T + RENT<br><br><i>Down</i><br>1. CHASES: CHA[i]SES<br>2. RACKS: [c]RACKS<br>3. MERV: ME + R.V.<br>4. B. + EATS<br>5. foresT REEstablishment <i>&lit.</i><br>8. KEPT: KE[m.]PT<br>9. EASED: [c]EASED<br>12. HERB: HE + R&B<br>13. YANKEE: (KENYA)* + E[thiopia]<br>15. (NEARS)* <br>16. SATAN: S(A)TAN <i>As in Stan Lee.</i><br>18. [p]EONS <i>or</i> [n]EONS<br>19. F. + EAR",
